Cook,<br><br>
Funny thing about you realizing the enemy was trying to kill you. HA! That was about the only thing that was predictable and understandable with the whole mess!<br><br>
I look back on all the threads on this site, and everything that has been written over the past year, and I see nothing more than continued confusion and debate.  One thing is constant, however, and that's US!<br><br>
At the risk of becomming even more angry, I am starting McMaster's 'Dereliction of Duty'. On the cover are Johnson and McNamara. Puke. As I said before, both McNamara and Jane Fonda should be hung in a cage over the Reflecting Pool and subjected to public abuse, ridicule, and humiliation. We can put Johnson, and a few others, in a pork barrel, and send them over Niagra Falls.<br><br>
What impresses me about that whole gang, including the Military leadership, is the extent to which greed, power, corruption, and just plain no ethics, motivated them. In the end, everyone got what they wanted. The brass its medals and career opportunities, the politicians their local pork barrel votes, and industry tons of cash. We got nothing. I remember my &quot;Certificate of Appreciation&quot; from Nixon that they shoved in my hand when I got off the plane. I used it in the bathroom.<br><br>
...and then it just got all plowed under like it never happened!<br><br>
I guess I am just plain seething angry underneath it all. MTF saw it right away when we met. Maybe I should become a 'protestor' or an activist and channel this anger into kicking ass where it will do the most good right now.<br><br>
Now that's a thought!<br><br>
In between flashbacks and depression swings, there is a little room. Damn, we are a study in extremes, aren't we?<br><br>
